<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-27T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-27T06:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3664: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="from">Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-27T12:00:00+01:00">January 27, 1932—noon [<hi rend="italic">4 p.m.?</hi>]</date><lb/>[Received 2:10
                                p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>44. Department’s unnumbered telegram December 11, 2 p.m.<note n="57" xml:id="d85fn57">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>In view of undue strain put upon <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> to inform me personally of developments in
                                private meetings of the Council, Consulate’s 38, January 26, 9
                                    p.m.,<note n="57" xml:id="d85fn1">Not printed.</note> he has
                                arranged for <persName corresp="#p_SA1">Sweetser</persName> to do
                                this in a manner similar to <persName corresp="#p_SA1">Sweetser</persName>’s services in Paris to <persName corresp="#p_DGCG1">General Dawes</persName> in this
                                respect.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>In conformity with instructions in your 20, January 21, 4 p.m., I
                                am, however, keeping in personal contact with pertinent
                                officials.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_GPB1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>